data.title: Henry Cuellar indictment places his South Texas congressional seat in jeopardy
data.meta_description: South Texas Democratic Rep. Henry Cuellar and his wife were indicted on bribery charges Friday.
data.text: Here & Now host Robin Young speaks with Washington Post Texas politics reporter Patrick Svitek about the indictment of South Texas Democratic Rep. Henry Cuellar and his wife on bribery charges on Friday. Cuellar had been expected to cruise to re-election in November but now that's in question, and it's putting Democratic Party leaders in a bind.
